<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 05-03-01 - Ride Height Control Valve used with International Ride Optimized Suspension (IROS) and
        Hendrickson Air Suspension (HAS), without Code 14899, may not Re-Inflate the Air Springs Due to Blockage in the
        Dump Port
    </stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi050301" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>05-03-01</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>April, 2005</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>SPRINGS</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Ride Height Control Valve used with International Ride Optimized Suspension (IROS) and Hendrickson
                Air Suspension (HAS), without Code 14899, may not Re-Inflate the Air Springs Due to Blockage in the Dump
                Port
            </subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <distribution dealer="yes" fleet="yes" bodybuilder="no" isis_cd="yes"/>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>FE 300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>RE 200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>RE 300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4400</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>7300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>7400</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>7500</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>7600</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>7700</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8500</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8600</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9200I</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9400I</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9900I</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9900IX</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>International has received many claims for replacement of the ride height control valve not
                    re-inflating the air suspension springs. International IROS and Hendrickson HAS suspensions utilize
                    a Hadley height control valve with an integral dump feature. The vehicles that were built
                    <emph type="bold">without</emph>
                    the in-cab air control switch feature, Code 14899, require the suspension height control valve to
                    have a 3 inch hose in the dump port.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <partsinfo>
            <table id="t050301">
                <tgroup cols="3" align="center">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.84*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.28*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="0.88*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Part Number</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Description</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Quantity</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>417196C3</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1/4 Inch OD Hose, Bulk</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>As Required</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check dump port for the presence of a vent hose (Figure 1, Item 2).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If vent hose is not present, check if the dump port (Figure 1, Item 1) has a plug. If
                    the dump port has a plug, remove and discard the plug and install a 1/4 inch OD x 3 inch long hose
                    into the dump port.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the dump port does not have a plug, check for and clear any debris that may have
                    accumulated inside the dump port and install a 1/4 inch OD x 3 inch long hose into the dump port.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check for proper operation.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the height control valve does not operate properly, replace the valve. Install the
                    1/4 inch OD x 3 inch long vent hose into the new control valve dump port (Figure 1, Item 2).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0503011" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0503011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Height Control Valve Dump Port with Vent Hose</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Dump Port</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Dump Port Vent Hose</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
</isis>
